This is basically an infomercial.  Infomercials suck UNLESS you&#039;re actually interested in what they&#039;re selling.  In this case, you&#039;ll get a taste of squarefoot gardening.  Then you can decide if the book is worth it or not.


The production value is low.  The content is good... not great.  I&#039;m posting it because it gave me cause to completely re-think how we set up our garden and we&#039;re a bit more excited this season to try some new shit (no pun intended).

Definitely not worth buying though.  Don&#039;t feel bad for a second stealing this one.
